stories_text_raw:
As a user, I want to redesign the Resources page, so that it matches the new Broker design styles.
As a testing manager, I want to report user testing findings to agencies, so that they are informed of the insights for UX improvements.
As a design team member, I want to start the next round of edits for the specified pages, so that the design iterations continue smoothly.
As a developer, I want to log actions performed during the process, so that we have an accurate record of user activities and system actions.
As a submission manager, I want to update the status of submissions, so that the current state of submissions is accurately reflected.
As a data validator, I want to upload and validate files, so that only valid CSV files are accepted into the system.
As a file manager, I want to access published FABS files, so that I can retrieve necessary documents for review.
As a grant administrator, I want to ensure that only grant records are sent to the grant records system, so that the data remains clean and accurate.
As a compliance officer, I want to update validation rules, so that the system complies with the latest standards and requirements.
As a GTAS administrator, I want to add GTAS window data to the database, so that it is available for reporting and analysis.
As a request manager, I want to cache D File generation requests, so that duplicate requests are managed efficiently.
As a user experience lead, I want to create a user testing summary, so that we can document findings and improvements based on user feedback.
As a testing coordinator, I want to schedule user testing sessions, so that we can effectively plan and execute usability tests.
As a system administrator, I want to reset environment permissions, so that the environment is set up correctly for staging and testing purposes.
